PNEUMONIC PLAGUE - ECUADOR
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 1998 08:24:56 -0400 (EDT)
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>

According to press reports (El Comercio Quito 4/27), since the middle of
March there have been 12 deaths due to pneumonic plague in an indigenous
community in the province of Chimborazo. No source has been identified.
